Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by the State, defense counsel and defendant. Additional statements by: Jasmine D.

As to Count 1:
The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 3.5 YEARS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 2 YEARS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 1.5 YEARS, concurrent to Counts 2 & 3, credit for 135 days.

As to Count 2:
The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 3.5 YEARS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 2 YEARS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 1.5 YEARS, concurrent to Counts 1 & 3, credit for 0 days.

As to Count 3:
The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 3.5 YEARS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 2 YEARS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 1.5 YEARS, concurrent to Counts 2 & 1, credit for 0 days.

Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.

-Restitution set at zero
-Court costs and victim/witness surcharges are to be paid from up to 25% of prison funds, balance to be paid by 11/19/2017; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment.
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge from up to 25% of prison funds, balance to be paid by 11/19/2017; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers
-Employment or school
-Successfully complete a Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Modification Program
-Successfully complete a Parenting Program

Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon he may no longer use or possess any firearms or body armor; also he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been restored.

Defendant Rodney J Shackleford in court with attorney James E Toran.  Defendant Rodney J Shackleford in custody.  Laura A Crivello appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for motion hearing, however defense requests to proceed with plea and sentencing.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.
